{"id": 232019608, "title": "Robber threatens Kilmarnock shop staff before carrying out terrifying raid", "text": "Detectives have launched a hunt for a Kilmarnock shop robber who threatened staff before fleeing with items. Police have launched a major investigation into the terrifying raid on the Meiklewood Road store, which took place last night at 7.10pm. The suspect entered the shop and threatened a member of staff before making off with items. The man is described as being of slim build, wearing a black jacket, a grey hooded top, black tracksuit bottoms and black trainers. Detective constable Shawnie McGeechan said: \u201cOur enquiries are ongoing and we are appealing to anyone who may have witnessed anything to contact us. \u201cWe also ask anyone with private CCTV or dashcam footage of the area at the time to come forward.\u201d Anyone with information is asked to contact police on 101 quoting incident 3103 of 8 June, 2024, or call Crimestoppers anonymously on 0800 555 111. Read next: Scotland fan sees Euros song become 'unofficial' Tartan Army anthem for Germany Coffee shop boss has 'mixed emotions' as new owners take charge Bowling alley and golf simulator plan lodged at former Ayrshire shop New boutique hotel and apartments to open in Prestwick this summer Construction work starts on \u00a37.8 million new housing project on site of former Ayrshire school Don't miss the latest Ayrshire headlines \u2013sign up to our free daily newsletter", "summary": "Detectives have launched a major probe into the shock incident.", "url": "https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/ayrshire/robber-threatens-kilmarnock-shop-staff-32992814", "image": "https://i2-prod.dailyrecord.co.uk/incoming/article30688478.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/363629996_762251628921012_4404694371466117571_n.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 14:53:34", "author": "Ross Dunn", "authors": ["Ross Dunn"], "language": "en", "catgory": "politics", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.138}